#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:2
msgid "First steps"
msgstr "第一步"

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:4
msgid ""
"In this set of articles, you’ll learn the **core fundamentals** of Nest. "
"To get familiar with the essential building blocks of Nest applications, "
"we’ll build a basic CRUD application with features that cover a lot of "
"ground at an introductory level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:10
msgid "Language"
msgstr "语言"

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:12
msgid ""
"We’re in love with `TypeScript <http://www.typescriptlang.org/>`__, but "
"above all - we love `Node.js <https://nodejs.org/en/>`__. That’s why Nest"
" is compatible with both TypeScript and **pure JavaScript**. Nest takes "
"advantage of the latest language features, so to use it with vanilla "
"JavaScript we need a `Babel <http://babeljs.io/>`__ compiler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:18
msgid ""
"We’ll mostly use TypeScript in the examples we provide, but you can "
"always **switch the code snippets** to vanilla JavaScript syntax (simply "
"click to toggle the language button in the upper right hand corner of "
"each snippet)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:24
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr "先决条件"

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:26
msgid ""
"Please make sure that `Node.js <https://nodejs.org/>`__ (>= 8.9.0) is "
"installed on your operating system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:30
msgid "Setup"
msgstr "建立"

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:32
msgid ""
"Setting up a new project is quite simple with the `Nest CLI "
"</cli/overview>`__. With `npm <https://www.npmjs.com/>`__ installed, you "
"can create a new Nest project with the following commands in your OS "
"terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/first-steps.rst:42
msgid ""
"The ``project`` directory will be created, node modules and a few other "
"boilerplate files will be installed, and a ``src/`` directory will be "
"created and populated with several core files."
msgstr ""

